      <title>家庭教育激增，但宽松的监管可能使孩子容易受到虐待</title>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2024/01/18/1225324564/home-schooling-is-surging-but-lax-regulation-can-leave-kids-vulnerable-to-abuse</link>
      <description><![CDATA[家庭教育现在是美国发展最快的教育形式，但《华盛顿邮报》记者彼得·贾米森指出，“值得注意的是，对在家接受教育的儿童的监督如此之少。”]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.npr.org/2024/01/18/1225324564/home-schooling-is-surging-but-lax-regulation-can-leave-kids-vulnerable-to-abuse</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 18 Jan 2024 18:30:50 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>研究发现，美国有色人种儿童的医疗保健状况普遍较差</title>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2024/01/18/1225270442/health-inequities-pediatrics-kids-of-color-disparities</link>
      <description><![CDATA[研究人员发现，从新生儿和初级保健到急诊医学，儿童获得的护理质量低于白人同龄人。差异包括手术后等待时间更长和止痛药物减少。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2024/01/18/1225270442/health-inequities-pediatrics-kids-of-color-disparities</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 18 Jan 2024 18:04:46 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
